            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan with the <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and a good grind of <strong>pepper</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for a further 8-10 min or until starting to thicken</p><p>Once thickened, add the <strong>drained spaghetti</strong> to the sauce with a splash of <strong>starchy water</strong> and cook for a final 1-2 min or until fully combined – this is your<strong> veg-packed tomato spaghetti</strong></p>",
